description: Recognized today as both a singer and an actress, the artist still appears affected by the attacks she suffered early during her fame. description: The US State Department revoked the visas of dozens of members of the Palestinian Authority and the Palestine Liberation Organization. President Abbas himself could be prevented from traveling to New York. The Trump administration said that Palestinian leaders are 'undermining the prospects for peace.'

description: Washington's step comes as France is leading a push to recognize the Palestinian state at the gathering of world leaders in New York.

headline: China prepares for major military parade to assert power and commemorate history
description: The capital will host a spectacular parade on Wednesday, September 3, marking 80 years since the victory over Japanese aggression. Against a tense international backdrop, Beijing intends to showcase its power and revive its historical memory, while strengthening its alliances.

headline: Ultra-processed foods cause negative health effects within weeks, study finds
description: In a clinical trial similar to those used for testing medicines, scientists studied the health impacts of a diet filled with ultra-processed foods. Results show that numerous biological processes are affected.

description: 'The Enigma of Mohammed VI' (6/6). His status as 'commander of the faithful' has given the Moroccan king a unique aura and has enabled him to push back against the ambitions of Islamists, whose political project and way of life he rejects.

headline: Air quality in Paris: Monitoring agency reports significant improvement over 10 years

headline: Mohammed VI, the makhzen and the art of palace secrecy
description: 'The Enigma of Mohammed VI' (5/6). In order to maintain his power, the Moroccan monarch relies on a handful of loyal supporters, most of whom he has known for decades.
